title: For Sale:  H&K MR556 A1 in 5.56x45/.223 Remington
postcontent: A direct descendent of the HK416, the MR556A1 is a semi-automatic rifle developed by Heckler & Koch as a premium level commercial/civilian firearm with match rifle capability. Like the HK416, the MR556A1 is a major product improvement over conventional AR-type carbines and rifles. The MR556A1 uses the HK proprietary gas piston operating system, employing a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the gas tube normally found in AR15/M16/M4-style firearms. This method of operation virtually eliminates malfunctions that are common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area

title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer P-320 w/ extras
postcontent: This is a Sig P-320. It is the modular handgun system that the Military has decided on using since they have "retired" the Beretta M9 series. This Sig is in, as you can see, flat dark earth..both the frame and the slide. The FDE frame is a medium compact and it includes a black compact frame as well. There are two 15 round magazines for the medium FDE frame and one for the black compact frame. I have shot this Sig a little over 100 times. It has an awesome trigger...probably the best trigger that i've ever felt right out of the box. (which was one reason that the powers that be at the Pentagon chose this gun) For those that arent familiar with this series.. the trigger group itself is considered the "firearm" and has the serial # on it. The switch from the FDE frame to the black compact frame is very simple and once practiced a time or two can be done in less than a minute. This is a superbly accuracte pistol with both frames. The all FDE one is beautiful and the compact black frame (once changed) adds a nice contrast as well. The price is well under what you would pay for this setup..with both frames and 3 magazines, in all. I have carried it a few times but it hasn't been shot that much at all.. just wanted to see how accurate it was and how the trigger was. I love this pistol..just don't shoot it much so decided to take it out of the safe and let it go. Also, has the box and lock. I can't find the manual but You Tube has tons of technical stuff on it so the manual is really irrelevant.  Thanks for looking! God bless
